tweets_day_media.columns=['date', 'total']
tweets_day_politics = df[df.type == 'politics'].groupby('date')[['id']].count().reset_index()
tweets_day_politics.columns=['date', 'total']

In [6]:
def plot_countries(countries_sample):
    plt.rc("figure", figsize=(20, 10))
    for country in countries_sample:
        tweets_day = df[df.country == country].groupby('date')[['id']].count()
        tweets_day.columns=['total']
        b = sns.lineplot(x = "date", y = "total", data = tweets_day)
    loc = plticker.MultipleLocator(base=60.0) # To put a tick every seven days
    b.axes.set_title('Number of tweets by day', fontsize=40)
    b.set_xlabel("Date",fontsize=24)
    b.xaxis.set_major_locator(loc)
    b.set_ylabel("Number of tweets",fontsize=24)
    b.tick_params(labelsize=15)
    plt.legend(labels=countries_sample, fontsize = 20)
    plt.show()
